    <name>
      <text>Using logarithms with standard form</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Write the number \({@value@}\) in standard form using logarithms.</p>

<p>Express your answer in the form \(A \times 10^B\).</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>We want to express the number in standard form \(A \times 10^B\).</p>

<p>\({@value@} = {@coef@} \times 10^{@exp@}\).</p>

<p>Using logarithms:</p>

<p>\[
\log_{10}({@value@}) = \log_{10}({@coef@}) + \log_{10}(10^{@exp@})
\]</p>

<p>\[
= \log_{10}({@coef@}) + {@exp@}.
\]</p>

<p>Therefore the standard form is:</p>

<p>\[
{@coef@} \times 10^{@exp@}.
\]</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
